## **WEEK 14: Advanced Patterns**
**Theme:** "Idiomatic Rust"

### **Day 92**
- **Material:** Builder pattern
- **Reading:** Research builder pattern in Rust (15 min)
- **Exercise:** (15 min)
```rust
struct PackageBuilder {
    name: String,
    version: Option<String>,
}

impl PackageBuilder {
    fn new(name: String) -> Self {
        Self { name, version: None }
    }
    
    fn version(mut self, v: String) -> Self {
        self.version = Some(v);
        self
    }
    
    fn build(self) -> Package {
        Package {
            name: self.name,
            version: self.version.unwrap_or_else(|| "latest".to_string()),
        }
    }
}
```

### **Day 93**
- **Material:** `newtype` pattern
- **Exercise:** (30 min)
```rust
struct PackageName(String);

impl PackageName {
    fn new(s: String) -> Result<Self, MetapacError> {
        if s.is_empty() {
            Err(MetapacError::InvalidName)
        } else {
            Ok(PackageName(s))
        }
    }
}
```

### **Day 94**
- **Material:** Type state pattern
- **Reading:** Research compile-time state machines (15 min)
- **Exercise:** (15 min)
```rust
struct Uninstalled;
struct Installed;

struct Package<State> {
    name: String,
    _state: PhantomData<State>,
}

impl Package<Uninstalled> {
    fn install(self) -> Package<Installed> {
        // Can only call on Uninstalled packages
        Package { name: self.name, _state: PhantomData }
    }
}
```

### **Day 95**
- **Material:** `From` and `Into` traits
- **Exercise:** (30 min)
```rust
impl From<&str> for Package {
    fn from(s: &str) -> Self {
        Package { name: s.to_string() }
    }
}

let pkg: Package = "vim".into();
```

